Diane Priestley was struggling to breathe and was starting to turn blue . 
  David Priestley called 999 three times and had to wait an hour for an ambulance to reach his wife at her home in County Durham . 
  Investigation found ambulance should have been given a response priority of eight minutes . 
  North East Ambulance Service admitted delay was initially due to the call-handler error  . 
  Grandmother-of-nine died from a ruptured abdominal aortic aneurysm on arrival at hospital . 
 